{"PERT":[{"def":"Open; evident; apert.","pos":""},{"def":"Lively; brisk; sprightly; smart.","pos":""}],"PERTAIN":[{"def":"To belong; to have connection with, or dependence on, something, as an appurtenance, attribute, etc.","pos":""},{"def":"To have relation or reference to something.","pos":""}],"PERTEREBRATION":[{"def":"The act of boring through.","pos":""}],"PERTHIOCYANOGEN":[{"def":"Same as Persulphocyanogen.","pos":""}],"PERTHITE":[{"def":"A kind of feldspar consisting of a laminated intertexture of albite and orthoclase, usually of different colors.","pos":""}],"PERTINACIOUS":[{"def":"Holding or adhering to any opinion, purpose, or design, with obstinacy; perversely persistent; obstinate; as, pertinacious plotters; a pertinacious beggar.","pos":""},{"def":"Resolute; persevering; constant; steady.","pos":""}],"PERTINACITY":[{"def":"The quality or state of being pertinacious; obstinacy; perseverance; persistency.","pos":""}],"PERTINACY":[{"def":"The quality or state of being pertinent; pertinence.","pos":""}],"PERTINATELY":[{"def":"The quality or state of being pertinent; justness of relation to the subject or matter in hand; fitness; appositeness; relevancy; suitableness.","pos":""}],"PERTINENT":[{"def":"Belonging or related to the subject or matter in hand; fit or appropriate in any way; adapted to the end proposed; apposite; material; relevant; as, pertinent illustrations or arguments; pertinent evidence.","pos":""},{"def":"Regarding; concerning; belonging; pertaining.","pos":""}],"PERTLY":[{"def":"In a pert manner.","pos":""}],"PERTNESS":[{"def":"The quality or state of being pert.","pos":""}],"PERTRANSIENT":[{"def":"Passing through or over.","pos":""}],"PERTURB":[{"def":"To disturb; to agitate; to vex; to trouble; to disquiet.","pos":""},{"def":"To disorder; to confuse.","pos":""}],"PERTURBABILITY":[{"def":"The quality or state of being perturbable.","pos":""}],"PERTURBABLE":[{"def":"Liable to be perturbed or agitated; liable to be disturbed or disquieted.","pos":""}],"PERTURBANCE":[{"def":"Disturbance; perturbation.","pos":""}],"PERTURBATE":[{"def":"Perturbed; agitated.","pos":""}],"PERTURBATION":[{"def":"A disturbance in the regular elliptic or other motion of a heavenly body, produced by some force additional to that which causes its regular motion; as, the perturbations of the planets are caused by their attraction on each other.","pos":""}],"PERTURBATIONAL":[{"def":"Of or pertaining to perturbation, esp.","pos":""}],"PERTURBATIVE":[{"def":"Tending to cause perturbation; disturbing.","pos":""}],"PERTURBED":[{"def":"Agitated; disturbed; troubled.","pos":""}],"PERTURBER":[{"def":"One who, or that which, perturbs, or cause perturbation.","pos":""}],"PERTUSATE":[{"def":"Pierced at the apex.","pos":""},{"def":"Punched; pierced with, or having, holes.","pos":""}],"PERTUSION":[{"def":"The act of punching or piercing with a pointed instrument; as, pertusion of a vein.","pos":""}],"PERTUSSIS":[{"def":"The whooping cough.","pos":""}]}